Addition and subtraction are basically the same as what we know in decimal, with a few extra digits tossed in for flavor.
The trick is nothing more than knowing your addition tables up to 0FH. 
This is best done bot by thinking to yourself, "Now, if C is 12 and F is 15, then C + F is 12 + 15, which is 27 decimal but 1Bh." Instead, you should simply think, "C + F is 1BH."

It takes practice to learn to piano, and it takes practice to drive the core skills of assembly language programming down into your synapses where they belong. 

